Customer Retention & Churn Analysis (Telco)
ğŸ“Œ Project Overview
This project focuses on identifying the key drivers of customer churn for a subscription-based Telecommunications company. By analyzing customer demographics, account information, and service usage, I have developed a data-driven strategy to improve retention rates and increase Customer Lifetime Value (CLV).

ğŸ¯ Business Goals
Identify High-Risk Segments: Which customers are most likely to leave?

Uncover Churn Drivers: Why are they leaving? (e.g., pricing, contract types, or service issues).

Actionable Strategy: Provide concrete recommendations to the Product and Growth teams to reduce churn.

ğŸ“Š The Dataset
The analysis is based on the Telco Customer Churn dataset, containing information on 7,043 customers.

Target Variable: Churn (Customers who left within the last month).

Features: Services (Fiber Optic, Online Security, etc.), Account Info (Contract, Payment Method, Tenure), and Demographics.

ğŸ› ï¸ Tech Stack
Data Cleaning: Python (Pandas) / Power BI Power Query

Analysis: Python (Seaborn, Matplotlib)

Dashboarding: Power BI Desktop

Documentation: Markdown

ğŸ“ˆ Key Insights & Dashboard
1. The "Contract" Effect
Insight: Customers on Month-to-month contracts have a churn rate of over 40%, compared to <7% for two-year contracts.

Recommendation: Incentivize long-term commitments through "Loyalty Discounts" or value-added bundles.

2. The First-Year "Danger Zone"
Insight: The highest volume of churn occurs within the first 12 months of tenure.

Recommendation: Implement a 90-day "Customer Success" onboarding program to ensure users are finding value early.

3. Service-Specific Friction
Insight: Fiber Optic users churn at a significantly higher rate than DSL users, despite paying a premium. This indicates a potential gap in service quality or price-to-value perception.

Recommendation: Conduct a technical audit of Fiber service stability and offer complimentary "Tech Support" for high-tier plans.

ğŸš€ How to Replicate this Analysis
Clone the Repo: git clone https://github.com/your-username/churn-analysis-project.git

Data Cleaning: Run the Data_Cleaning.ipynb notebook to see how missing values and data types were handled.

Power BI: Open the .pbix file located in the /dashboard folder to interact with the visual reports.

ğŸ’¡ Practical Recommendations for the Business
Switch to Auto-Pay: Customers using Electronic Checks churned at nearly 2x the rate of those on Automatic Bank Transfers. Offer a $2 monthly credit for switching to Auto-Pay.

Bundle "Sticky" Services: Customers with Online Security and Tech Support had significantly lower churn rates. Focus marketing efforts on bundling these into basic packages.

